action: optimize
reasoning: "Final iteration (3/3) with Q3 being 12.3x slower than DuckDB and dominating 79.9% of execution time. Clear technical debt (std::unordered_map, unused zone maps, no SIMD) with high-impact, low-risk fixes available. Selecting top 4 priorities targeting 8-12x speedup on Q3 and 2.5x on Q6 to close gap with DuckDB (current 1458ms → target 250-350ms vs DuckDB's 213ms)."
selected_recommendations[4]: 0,1,2,4
focus_areas[4]: "Replace std::unordered_map with open-addressing hash tables in Q3 for 3-4x speedup via cache-friendly memory access",Implement zone map block skipping for Q3 date filters (skip 49% of blocks) for 1.5-2x additional speedup,Add zone map block skipping to Q6 multi-column predicates (skip 85% of blocks) for 2-2.5x speedup,SIMD-vectorize Q3 date filtering using AVX-512 (_mm512 intrinsics) for 1.3-1.5x additional speedup
strategy_notes: "Being aggressive on final iteration. Priorities 1+2+5 compound for ~8-12x total speedup on Q3 (1164ms → 100-170ms, approaching DuckDB's 95ms). Priority 3 brings Q6 to near-parity with DuckDB. All optimizations leverage underutilized hardware (zone maps in storage design, AVX-512 CPU support) with no re-ingestion required. Expected total time: 250-350ms vs DuckDB's 213ms - competitive performance."
notes: "Combined optimization strategy: (1) Fix Q3's cache-unfriendly hash tables with open-addressing + pre-sizing, (2) Enable zone map pruning on both Q3 and Q6 to skip 49-85% of blocks, (3) Add AVX-512 SIMD to Q3 date filters for 16-way parallelism. These are the highest ROI optimizations available with low risk and clear implementation paths."